-- Dubai’s Takaful Emarat Starts Equity Fund, CEO Marrouche Says
-- B y   D a n a   E l   B a l t a j i   a n d   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-03-05T08:22:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-05/dubai-s-takaful-emarat-starts-equity-fund-ceo-marrouche-says.html
Takaful Emarat - Insurance P.S.C., a
Dubai-based Shariah-compliant life and health insurance company,
started a 20 million Saudi riyal ($5.3 million) equity fund,
Chief Executive Officer Ghassan Marrouche said.  “It’s a global equity investment fund that protects 90
percent of the capital,” he said in an interview in Dubai
today. “The expected annual rate of return is between 3 to 5
percent.” The fund is managed by Riyad Capital, Marrouche said.  Takaful Emarat’s services include savings through
investment products, personal accident benefits and mortgage
insurance products.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Dana El Baltaji in Dubai at 
